{# Multi-regime cross-cutting report (Plan 4 §T14, spec §9.7).

   Rendered by T15's ``firm eval --regime all`` after every regime's
   ``run_regime`` has completed. Loops over a list of regime-summary
   dicts, then emits ONE aggregated PROCESS METRICS block + the
   hard-coded NOT MEASURED block.

   Context contract (T15 must produce):

     regimes              : list[dict] — one entry per regime, each with:
                              regime_number : int   (1-based)
                              header_dates  : str   ("Mon dd–dd, YYYY")
                              description   : str   ("earnings-heavy")
                              perf          : dict  (same shape as regime.md.j2)
     aggregated_metrics   : list[MetricResult] — cross-regime aggregation in
                              spec §9.5 order. The labelling + formatting
                              rules mirror regime.md.j2.

   This template intentionally does NOT depend on the runner-side context
   shape used by regime.md.j2 — T15 owns the wiring and may reshape per
   regime before calling here.
#}
{%- set labels = {
    "groundedness": "Groundedness",
    "decision_discipline": "Decision discipline",
    "citation_diversity": "Citation diversity",
    "reversal_rate": "Reversal rate",
    "risk_policy_compliance": "Privileged-action attempts",
    "hitl_correctness": "HITL correctness",
    "schema_rejections": "Schema rejections",
    "red_team_pass": "Red-team pass",
    "sufficiency_gate": "Sufficiency gate",
    "failure_mode_coverage": "FailureMode coverage",
} -%}
{%- set pct_metrics = ("groundedness", "reversal_rate") -%}
EVAL REPORT — Replay smoke test across 3 regimes
{% for r in regimes %}
REGIME {{ r.regime_number }}: {{ r.header_dates }} ({{ r.description }})
  {{ "%-23s"|format("Total return:") }} {{ "%+.1f"|format(r.perf.total_return_pct) }}%
  {{ "%-23s"|format("vs SPY (primary):") }} {{ "%+.1f"|format(r.perf.vs_spy_pp) }}pp (SPY: {{ "%+.1f"|format(r.perf.spy_return_pct) }}%)
  {{ "%-23s"|format("vs equal-weight basket:") }} {{ "%+.1f"|format(r.perf.vs_basket_pp) }}pp (basket: {{ "%+.1f"|format(r.perf.basket_return_pct) }}%)
  {{ "%-23s"|format("Per-trade returns:") }} {{ r.perf.per_trade_returns_str }}
  {{ "%-23s"|format("Hit rate:") }} {{ r.perf.hit_rate_str }}
{% endfor %}
PROCESS METRICS (aggregated)
{%- for m in aggregated_metrics %}
{%- set label = labels.get(m.name, m.name) %}
{%- if m.name in pct_metrics %}
  {{ "%-30s"|format(label ~ ":") }} {{ "%.1f"|format(m.value) }}%
{%- else %}
  {{ "%-30s"|format(label ~ ":") }} {{ m.value }}
{%- endif %}
{%- endfor %}

NOT MEASURED
  - Investment quality / alpha — N too small
  - Generalization beyond 3 declared regimes
  - Real-world fill quality — paper sim
  - Forward references inside chunks — known RAG limitation
  - Long-horizon learning effects — journal too sparse
